    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ensembles of Southeast Asia, consisting of various combinations of gongs, metallophones, xylophones, drums, bowed and plucked chordophones, flutes or double reed aerophones, small cymbals, and singers. They accompany dances and religious and ceremonial events.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Conjuntos del sudeste de Asia, consistentes en varias combinaciones de gongs, metalófonos, xilófonos, tambores, crodófonos con arco y de punteo, flautas o aerófonos de lengüeta doble, pequeños címbalos y cantantes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ensembles uit Zuidoost-Azië, bestaande uit gevarieerde combinaties van gongs, metallofonen, xylofoons, drums, strijk- en tokkelchordofonen, fluiten of dubbelriet aërofonen, kleine bekkens en zangers. Ze begeleiden dansen en religieuze en plechtige evenementen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>東南亞的合奏樂團，由銅鑼、鐵琴、木琴、鼓、弓弦與撥弦弦樂器、笛子或雙簧管樂器、小鈸以及歌手等各種組合所組成。他們在舞蹈以及宗教與典禮活動中擔任伴奏。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
